{
  "texts": [
    "When leading a company with a less adaptable organizational resource configuration for TMTdriven AI adoption (e.g., an incumbent), TMTs can proactively allocate their efforts to eliminate obstacles that might limit the TMT's influence.",
    "This could involve strategically prioritizing the development of a data-centric culture during AI implementation (Toutaoui et al., 2022).",
    "Moreover, executives often need to assess other firms, like competitors, suppliers, or acquisition targets.",
    "When assessing such firms, one can leverage our findings regarding firm type's moderating effect to inform one's judgment of a firm's AI adoption potential.",
    "Such informed judgments might also prove valuable information when forming partnerships in a business network aiming to combine the advantages of different firm types (Steiber & Alänge, 2020)."
  ]
}